Clear sky- wind NW  less than  5 mph.

Partly cloudy- wind SW about 5 mph.
Partly sunny- wind w-northwest about 5 mph.

Partly sunny.  Wind SW  less than 5 mph.

Partly cloudy- wind W about 5 mph.
Mostly cloudy- wind NW  greater than 5 mph.
Partly cloudy- calm.  Last report for 1994.
Mostly cloudy- wind E 0-5 mph.  Our dam repair project is scheduled to start about 1 August.
Clear- hazy sunshine- wind n-northwest 5+ mph.
Clear skies- wind SW at 5 mph.  Hot. dam repair starts on or about 14 August 1995.
Partly cloudy- wind SE 0-5 mph.  Lake will be lowered 1' in a week or so for dam repair.

Public perception also due to low water levels and lots of rain.  Clear- wind NW 5-10 mph.  Dam repair started 8/14.  Water level at low water mark.  About 9.7" of rain since 8/1 about 6.2" since 8/ ( ) .
Clear sky- wind 0-3 mph from west.
Clear sky- little or no wind. humid + hazy.
Sunny- wind south less 5 mph- 2 " rain on 6/19- 1.75" on 6/21.
Partly cloudy- gentle east breeze- .50" of rain in the morning.
Sunny and calm- 3.6 inches of rain on July 16th.
Partly cloudy variable breezes.  2.8" rain on 6/11/98.
Partly cloudy NE wind 5 mph.  1.35" rain on 8/17/98.
Clear NW wind 5 mph.  0.8" rain on 8/22/98.
Sunny and easterly wind less than five mph.

Water temp 77 F.  Partly cloudy- southerly breeze- and 1.8" of rain on 7/8.

Clear- west wind.  Adult osprey fishing.
Judy Foster - Helper. Extremely hot. No measureable rainfall since 06/20/2012
Helper - Judy Foster - Hot + dry - No measureable rain since 6/20/2012
Judy Foster - Helper - Some drought relief - About .6" rain since 7/14.
Judy Foster - Helper       Julia + Trevor Foster (Grandchildren) - Helpers
Judy Foster - Helper.......This will be our last reading for 2012
Assisted by Judy Foster - Partly cloudy- but bright.
Assisted by Judy Foster Beautiful- cool sunny day
Beautiful- sunny fall day. Slight southerly breeze. Assister by Judy Foster
Assited by Judy Foster. Another beautiful fall day! The water is calm. We saw a bald eagle soaring over the lake. This is the final reading for this season. See you in the spring!
Assisted by Judy Foster. Beaver activity in channel between Lakes B + C. Water very brackish.
Assisted by Judy Foster. Lake still very brackish. Heavy rain on 6/1/2014 2.6"

Assisted by Judy Foster. Water is starting to clear- but still very brackish. Water appears to have a lot of suspended particulate in it. Last week the presence of Zebra Mussels was confirmed in Lake Morris by the DNR.
Assisted by Judy Foster. Water in Lakes C+D still brackish.
Assisted by Judy Foster. Zebra Mussel monitoring plates installed July 26- 2014 on my pier by Golden Sands R+D
Assisted by Judy Foster - Water very brown due to heavy June rains.
